<h2>About Risley Shops</h2>

<hr />
<p>Risley provides community members with 12 artist workshops that range from letterpress, to wood shop, to jewelry making. &nbsp;We have a system of managers and coordinators who ensure the safe use of the shops, and can provide assistance in a variety of artistic endeavors. &nbsp;Shops are only available for Risley residents and Out-of-House members, and can be accessed at the times listed below. &nbsp;Please observe all shop rules and regulations when using the shops, and please leave the space in the same or better condition as you found it!&nbsp;</p>

<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><i>For more information about the shops visit <a href="http://orgsync.rso.cornell.edu/org/risleyasub">A-Sub&#39;s Website</a>!</i></strong></p>

<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>

<h2><strong>Shop Coordinators</strong></h2>

<hr />
<p>Shop coordinators are students within Risley who are familiar with and trained in the art mediums which they oversee. &nbsp;Shop coordinators work directly with shop managers to ensure the upkeep and safe use of our shops. &nbsp;Shop coordinators and their respective areas of expertise for the 2016-2017 academic year are&nbsp;listed below. &nbsp;</p>

<table align="left" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:500px;">
